Description: Fragment of oval handle to moderate turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Traces of red paint. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine pink-buff; red core; cream slip..
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), 31, 51. Name Xenophanes. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 045.53.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0862)
